    Default Keybindings:
        Ctrl+C          - Copy
        Ctrl+X          - Cut
        Ctrl+V          - Paste
        Ctrl+S          - Save
        Ctrl+F          - Find/Search
        Ctrl+E          - Open Command Bar
        Alt+G           - Toggle Cheat Sheet
        Shift+Arrow Keys - Make Selection
    
    Command Bar:
        Ctrl+E                      - Open Command Bar
        Alt+G                       - Toggle Nano-like Cheat Sheet
        Type 'help defaultkeys'     - View Default Keybindings
        Type 'help commands'        - List Available Commands
        Press Tab                   - Auto-complete Commands
        Type a few letters + Tab    - Filter Commands
    
    Common Commands:
        save [filename]             - Save as (Ctrl+S if filename omitted)
        replace foo bar [flags]     - Replace "foo" with "bar"
                                      Flags:
                                        -a  Replace all occurrences
                                        -l  Literal search instead of regex
        replaceall foo bar          - Replace all occurrences of "foo" with "bar"
        vsplit [filename]           - Split window vertically
        hsplit [filename]           - Split window horizontally
        tab [filename]              - Open filename in a new tab
        goto 123                    - Go to line 123
                                      (Negative numbers go from file end)
        term [command]              - Open terminal and run command
                                      (Omit command to open default shell)
        set [option] [value]        - Change option permanently
        setlocal [option] [value]   - Change option temporarily
        show [option]               - Display current value of option
        bind [keycombo] [action]    - Set custom keybinding
    
    Options:
        autoindent       - true
            Automatically use same indentation as previous line.
        autosave=X       - Set autosave interval in seconds (0 to disable).
        autosu           - Automatically elevate with sudo if needed for saving.
        backup           - true
            Keep backups for all open buffers.
        clipboard        - external | terminal | internal
            external: Interact with system clipboard.
            terminal: Use terminalâ€™s clipboard (supports SSH).
            internal: Use Micro-specific clipboard.
        hlsearch         - Highlight all search matches.
        eofnewline       - true
            Automatically add newline at end of file if missing.
        matchbrace       - true
            Underline matching braces when cursor is on one.
        ruler            - true
            Display line numbers.
        softwrap         - false
            Wrap long lines at screen edge.
        wordwrap         - false
            Wrap long lines by words (requires softwrap).
    
    Plugin Management:
        plugin list                 - List all installed plugins.
        plugin install [plugin]     - Install specified plugin.
        plugin remove [plugin]      - Remove specified plugin.
        plugin update [plugin]      - Update specified plugin.
        plugin update               - Update all plugins.
        plugin search 'keyword'     - Search for plugins by keyword.
        plugin available            - Show all available plugins.
    
    Default Plugins:
        autoclose    - Automatically add closing brackets and quotes.
        comment      - Comment/uncomment lines or selections.
        diff         - Show changes from latest Git commit.
        ftoptions    - Filetype-specific options (e.g., indentation).
        linter       - Linting support for multiple languages.
        literate     - Advanced syntax highlighting for Literate coding.
        status       - Extensions to the status line.
    
    Setting Options:
        Via Command Bar:
            set [option] [value]          - Permanently set option.
            setlocal [option] [value]     - Temporarily set option for current buffer.
            show [option]                 - Display current option value.
        Via settings.json:
            micro ~/.config/micro/settings.json
            Example to disable ruler:
            {
                "ruler": false
            }
            (Ensure proper JSON syntax with commas.)
    
    Custom Keybindings:
        Using Command Bar:
            bind [Ctrl-v] Copy
            bind [Ctrl-c] Paste
        Example for mouse binding:
            bind CtrlMouseLeft SelectLine
        Binding Key Sequences:
            bind <Ctrl-j><Ctrl-b> JumpToMatchingBrace
        Chaining Commands:
            bind "command:setlocal wordwrap on,command:setlocal softwrap on" Alt+z
            bind "command:setlocal wordwrap off,command:setlocal softwrap off" Alt+Z
    
    Multi-cursor Support:
        Alt-n            - Create new multiple cursor from selection
        Alt-Shift-Up     - Spawn cursor on the line above
        Alt-Shift-Down   - Spawn cursor on the line below
        Alt-p            - Remove the latest multiple cursor
        Alt-c            - Remove all multiple cursors (cancel)
        Alt-x            - Skip multiple cursor selection
        Alt-m            - Spawn cursors at the beginning of each line in selection
        Ctrl+MouseLeft   - Place a multiple cursor at any location
    
    Additional Features:
        - Mouse Support:
            Drag to create selection, double-click to select word, triple-click to select line.
        - Syntax Highlighting:
            Supports over 130 languages with customizable color schemes.
        - Highly Customizable:
            Rebind any key or change default settings via bindings.json or Command Bar.
        - Advanced Features:
            Access a wide range of functionalities through the Command Bar without memorizing all keybindings.

